<dl id="n53083k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53083k">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53083k"> 83(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> metanoia, <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53083k"><li>FW 341.30 </li><li><a href="../../flex/md/lexmd.htm#n53083k">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/md/l39md.htm#n53083k">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53083k">MS BL 47480-111</ms> </li><li>JJA 55:200 <a name="mdd6dash" href="../../ff/fdra/mda.htm#mdd6dash">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/md/mdd6.htm#n53083k">Draft: II.3&sect;4.6</a>' </li> </ul><mm class="note">Note: Classically speaking, sacramental confession consists in a penitent (or metanoiac) &mdash; after a diligent examination of his or her conscience &mdash; accusing himself of his or her sins to a priest invested with the power to remit sins. </mm> </dd></dl>
